            "title": "Welcome to the Everything2 community!",
            "from_address": "",
            "node_id": 275,
            "doctext": "<name>,\n<p>Welcome to Everything2, one of the internet's oldest and largest writing communities. You are receiving this message because someone gave this email address when registering on Everything2.</p>\n<p>We hope that you have registered because you like what you have read on Everything2 and want to contribute. If you have only read a little of the site, please take the time to explore it some more before making your own contribution. In principle, everything has a place on Everything2, but that doesn't mean there is a place for just any old thing. The links at the bottom of writeup pages are a useful way to take a random walk through the site and get a feel for it. You may also find <a href=\"http://<servername>/?node=E2 Quick Start\">E2 Quick Start</a> useful reading.</p>\n<p><b>Verifying your account</b></p>\n<p>To complete the registration process, click on the following link, or\ncopy and paste it into your web browser:</p>\n<p><a href=\"<verify_email_url>&amp;user_id=<user_id>&amp;validationkey=<validationkey>\"><verify_email_url>&amp;user_id=<user_id>&amp;validationkey=<validationkey></a></p>\n<p>If for some reason the link does not work, you can validate your\naccount manually: on any Everything2 page, enter \"Verify your email\naccount\" in the search box and click on the 'search' button. You will be taken to a page where you will be asked for your \nuser ID, which is  <b><user_id></b>, and your validation key, which is <b><validationkey></b>.</p>\n\n<p>All the best,</p>\n\nThe Everything2 Staff<br />\n<site_url></p>"
        },
